@realmoney Avoid The Asset Management Space I heard a lot of confident chatter in the financial media just now about why asset managers' shares are attractive now. I couldn't disagree more. The asset management business is being disrupted post haste - companies like $MS

charge enormous fees on overpriced and underperforming spread products. Their salad days are over. Asset managers are vulnerable to commoditization - which will take their investment management fees and product profit margins down dramatically in the years ahead.
@tomkeene @SquawkCNBC @cnbcfastmoney @riskreversal @guyadami @terranovajoe @ScottWapnerCNBC

Think of on-line trading as a template, foreshadowing aggressive fee competition ahead. And Katy Bar The Doors if we face a Bear Market.

The difference between money center banks (which I own) and asset management companies (which I am short) is that the former has near zero cost deposit bases. That is a profound difference. @ScottWapnerCNBC @cnbcfastmoney @terranovajoe

On line trading and asset management is getting commoditized - margins are disappearing. I have yet to hear substantive reasons to own $MS who's high priced spread products are especially vulnerable. @cnbcfastmoney @ScottWapnerCNBC @terranovajoe
